Twenty-six persons have been confirmed dead while search continued following a boat accident on Shagari River in Shagari local government area of Sokoto State. Chairman of Shagari Council area, Alhaji Aliyu Dantani, who disclosed the accident to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) yesterday, in Sokoto, said the incident occurred on Tuesday evening.   Four policemen killed, station burnt in Anambra     Eight containers of cutlasses, others seized at Lagos port     ‘Osinachi stayed in her marriage despite abuse’   Dantani said of the 26 recovered bodies, 21 were women while five were children, adding that a search and rescue mission was ongoing. The council boss, however, said the actual number of passengers on the boat could not be immediately ascertained. According to him, local divers were in the river to see how to either recover bodies or rescue survivors.